  "prompt": "Where can I learn Tai-Chi in Bangalore?",
  "response": "If you\u2019re looking to learn Tai-Chi in Bangalore, there are several options available depending on your preferences and location. Here are some places and resources where you can explore Tai-Chi classes:\n\n---\n\n### **Tai-Chi Classes and Instructors in Bangalore**\n1. **Chennai Martial Arts Academy (CMAG) - Bangalore Branch**  \n   - Offers Tai-Chi classes as part of their martial arts programs.  \n   - Contact: Check their website or social media pages for details.  \n\n2. **Art of Living International Center**  \n   - Sometimes organizes Tai-Chi workshops or classes as part of their wellness programs.  \n   - Location: 21st Km, Kanakapura Road, Udayapura.  \n   - Website: [www.artofliving.org](https://www.artofliving.org)  \n\n3. **Unakalki School of Tai Chi**  \n   - A dedicated Tai-Chi school in Bangalore offering classes for beginners and advanced learners.  \n   - Contact: Search for their website or social media presence.  \n\n4. **Yoga and Tai-Chi Studios**  \n   - Many yoga studios in Bangalore also offer Tai-Chi as part of their holistic wellness programs. Examples include:  \n     - **The Yoga House** (Indiranagar, Koramangala)  \n     - **Svastha Yoga** (Multiple locations)  \n\n5. **Community Centers and Parks**  \n   - Some community groups or instructors hold Tai-Chi sessions in public parks or community centers. Look for groups at:  \n     - **Cubbon Park**  \n     - **Lalbagh Botanical Garden**  \n\n6. **Online Platforms**  \n   - If in-person classes are not feasible, you can also explore online Tai-Chi courses through platforms like Udemy, Skillshare, or YouTube.\n\n---\n\n### **Tips for Finding Tai-Chi Classes**\n- **Search on Google or Social Media**: Use keywords like \"Tai-Chi classes in Bangalore\" to find updated listings.  \n- **Ask in Local Forums**: Platforms like Reddit (r/bangalore) or Facebook groups can help you find recommendations.  \n- **Contact Yoga Studios**: Many yoga studios in Bangalore may also offer Tai-Chi or know instructors who do.  \n\nLet me know if you\u2019d like help with specific areas in Bangalore! \ud83d\ude0a",
